ABIODUN Alabi, the CEO and founder of Toff Homes has unveiled two estates set for launch in two cities in the Southwest. According to the serial entrepreneur, the driving force for the latest packages being presented to the public focuses on striving for excellence in the sector. “There is a lot of development in the sector and we are determined to give our clients the best. At Toff, we are very zealous and passionate about creating impact and setting goals that we ensure come to reality “.   Owo massacre wake-up call to secure communities…     IBEDC appeals to Ogun communities over power outage     2023: Oke-Ogun people decry marginalisation   Alabi explained that the estates boost of the latest facilities in terms of innovations and technology. “We already acquired six estates but we would be launching two estates for now. The first is located at Epe and it is called TOFF Residence, while the second is located at Ido in Ibadan and it is called Eyitayo Estate.  Our plan is to launch the other four estates as times goes by and we are working tirelessly to ensure that quality and aesthetics is not compromised in any way.” He added that : “My desire for  knowledge and growth is my biggest driving force in my career and personal life .I crave to learn new things, do a lot of research and we have achieve a lot in terms of growth and development”.